    "description": "A variance-based global sensitivity analysis (Saltelli–Sobol method, N=2048 quasi-random samples via Sobol sequence) was conducted across eight uncertain input parameters: Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (CV 4.4%), yield strength (CV 3.4%), screw-rod contact friction coefficient (range 0.10–0.35), rod diameter tolerance (±0.05 mm), applied torque (±5%), cortical bone surrogate block modulus (CV 12%), fixture alignment angle (±0.5°), and crosshead displacement rate (±15%). First-order Sobol indices for construct stiffness QoI identified screw-rod contact friction coefficient (S1=0.41) and Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (S1=0.33) as dominant contributors, collectively accounting for 74% of output variance; yield force QoI was dominated by yield strength (S1=0.58) and friction coefficient (S1=0.22). Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interaction effects (ST–S1 < 0.05 for all parameters). These results directed targeted experimental characterization of friction coefficient via coupon-level tribology testing, reducing its uncertainty bound from ±0.125 to ±0.04 prior to final validation comparison.",
